The paper discusses acceleration methods for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses algorithm optimization and hardware-based improvement, which are relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses CNN architecture compression, which is relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
